	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
			<p>
				<add>German?</add>
			</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p>
				<add>את אחי אנוכי מבקש נסעו מזה</add>
			</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="align(right)">
				<placeName>Cleveland</placeName>
				<date>March 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1856</date>
			</p>
			<p>Dear Sir:</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">When I saw the first issue of the journal „Sinai<lb/> with headline
				„I am looking for my brothers”, I thought of<lb/> a cunning answer, namely „they
				have gone away from<lb/> here. This impelled me to do the <sic>vers</sic> which I
				wrote on<lb/> the opposite page.—</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">He asks to leave it printed in <persName>Lessers</persName>
				<add>?</add> paper.<lb/> If it is not printed there he will send it to the
				Israelite.<lb/> He also intends to make an essay on the <add>?</add> of
					<del>the</del><lb/> modern Jewism to the <sic>talmud</sic>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Signed</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">
				<persName role="author">Joseph Levi</persName>
			</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
			<p rend="align(center)">
				<hi rend="underline">Good Advice to Truth-Lovers</hi>
			</p>
			<p>Much noise from <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>, new things recently came,<lb/> A
				man called <persName>Einhorn</persName> invented them, their like has never
				been<lb/> heard.<lb/> Who is this man? What is his thought? <sic>people</sic> ask
				each other<lb/> But to me a thought comes stealthily, though it is a<lb/> thought of
				some importance,<lb/> That this man is himself confused, he lost his way.<lb/> He
				goes about calling, “My brethren I seek.”<lb/> [Beware!, lest he be to you a
				stumbling-block]<lb/> Do this, and live—say to him, “They have moved<lb/> away from
				here*”.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">(signed) Your brother <persName role="author">Joseph
					Halevi</persName></p>
			<p>*He refers here in a footnote to the explanation by <persName>Rashi</persName><lb/>
				of <hi rend="underline">Genesis 37:17</hi>. About this verse
					<persName>Rashi</persName> says that<lb/> the angels meaning was “They have
				given up their<lb/> brotherliness.”</p>
		</body>
